# Process and Signal in linux :- 
Process is the instance of the running program.
Signal is the short message send to the process.
ex- ctrl + C signal is used to interrupt the terminal.
Signals are used to interrupt, control, communicate with the process.
* process signal : means sending signal to running process to control their behaviour.
Two types of process signal :
1. Standard Signal - 
This are the predefined signals send to the running process. like start, stop, interrupt etc 
There are various types of standard signals :
A. SIGINT - signal interrupt
B. SIGTERM - signal terminate 
C. SIGKILL - signal kill 
D. SIGSTOP - signal stop 
E. SIGCONT - signal continue 
F. SIGSEGV - signal segmentation fault 

2. real time signal : 
this signal gives extra information along with signals.
like message or number
types : 
A. SIGRTMIN :
   This signal is the beginning of process.
   This mark the start point of service 
B. SIGRTMAX : 
   This is the highest point in the process.
   This can be the end of the service.
C. Intermediate signals :
   This are the signals in between this two signals.

